    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1867-06-03T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1867-06-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="288"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d288">
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Campbell</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                        Seward</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">New Orleans,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1867-06-03">
                            <hi rend="italic">June</hi> 3, 1867</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Presuming that President Juarez is now, or very soon will be, in the city of
                    Mexico, I propose to go there, via Vera Cruz, unless you instruct otherwise.
                    Cannot the revenue cutter Wilderness be directed to convey me to Vera Cruz? The
                    De Soto is also at this port.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>LEWIS D. CAMPBELL.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">William H. Seward,</hi>
                        <hi rend="italic">Secretary of State, Washington, D. C.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
